The paper deals with interference coordination in a heterogeneous cellular network (HetNet) with a focus on massive MIMO technology. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the mathematical foundations of communication and information processing. The paper also involves network architecture and optimization, which falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper proposes low-complexity interference coordination strategies, which can be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also deals with massive MIMO technology, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves optimization and game theory, which can be categorized under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
